Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm chips (peeling optional).

Pop the chips onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season well with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Toss to coat and spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Toss the @Diced Irish Chicken Breast{260%grams} with salt, pepper, @Ras-el-Hanout{1%sachet} and a drizzle of oil.

Place a pan over a medium-high heat.

Fry the chicken until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry! This is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @Red Kidney Beans{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

Mash the beans with a #fork{} (or #potato masher{}). Season with salt and pepper.

Chop the @Tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the beans.

Fry until warmed through, stirring regularly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir through the @Harissa Paste{1%sachet}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Pop the @Tortilla{8} into the oven to warm, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Mix the @Dried Chilli Flakes{2%sachets} (use less if you don't like spice) and @Yoghurt{75%grams} together in a small #bowl{}.

To assemble your tacos, divide the warmed tortillas between plates.

Top with the chicken, beans, tomato and a dollop of chilli yoghurt.

Finish with a drizzle of @Sweet Chilli Sauce{1%sachet}.

Serve the chicken tacos with the chips alongside.